OL,3,CMilburn warns of a lost generation
OL,4,Ctrapped by welfare and job shortages
OL,6,FBusinesses say the chancellor's
OL,7,Fdecision to raise employer National
OL,8,FInsurance contributions and the
OL,9,Fminimum wage in her first Budget has
OL,10,Fled to fewer jobs - particularly in
OL,11,Fpubs, bars, restaurants, hotels and
OL,12,Fretail.
OL,14,F"It definitely had an impact, there's
OL,15,Fno doubt about that," conceded
OL,16,FMilburn. "But what nobody should
OL,17,Fpretend is that somehow the problems
OL,18,Fyou're seeing in the youth labour
OL,19,Fmarket began in the last two years.
OL,20,FThey go back for at least two decades."
OL,26,@vD@AOUwD@UO]xD@JOU|D@gO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
